# UI Component Guidelines

## Component Structure
- Use the existing UI components from [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui/)
- Use proper TypeScript props interfaces
- Implement proper loading and error states

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- Follow the design system established in the UI components
- Use proper responsive design patterns
- Implement dark mode support where appropriate

## Card Components
- Use [Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardDescription, CardContent](mdc:components/ui/card.tsx) for content layout
- Follow the established card patterns for consistent UI
- Use proper spacing with `space-y-*` classes

## Button Components
- Use [Button](mdc:components/ui/button.tsx) with proper variants and sizes
- Implement proper disabled states for loading
- Use appropriate button variants (default, outline, secondary, etc.)

## Form Components
- Use [Input](mdc:components/ui/input.tsx) for form inputs
- Implement proper validation and error display
- Use proper form patterns with controlled components

## Layout Patterns
- Use proper semantic HTML structure
- Implement responsive design with proper breakpoints
- Use consistent spacing and typography
- Follow accessibility best practices